ential DoS vectors\n\n### Positive Security Aspects:\n- ✅ Uses `yaml.safe_load()` (not `yaml.load()`) - prevents code injection\n- ✅ Uses parameterized SQL queries throughout (no SQL injection)\n- ✅ Secrets stored in environment variables (not hardcoded)\n- ✅ Uses HTTPS for all external API calls\n- ✅ HTTP basic auth only used with HTTPS (Twilio API)\n- ✅ Uses httpx with timeout configuration\n- ✅ No eval(), exec(), or dynamic code execution\n- ✅ Proper input sanitization for regex patterns\n- ✅ Profile.yml correctly .gitignored for personal configuration\n\n### Recommendations Priority:\n1. **High Priority**: Fix SMTP environment variable handling (notify.py)\n2. **Medium Priority**: Add timeouts and certificate verification for SMTP\n3. **Low Priority**: Add path validation and redirect limiting for defense-in-depth\n\nThe codebase is relatively secure for a personal job scraper application, with most vulnerabilities being related to error handling and defense-in-depth rather than critical security flaws.\n",
